properties.Name: Pump
properties.Description: A device that is used to raise, transfer, deliver or compress fluids or that attenuates gases by suction, pressure or both.

Columns.Name: PumpId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Component.

Columns.Name: PumpDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the pump.

Columns.Name: CloseCoupledPumpIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the pump impeller is mounted directly on the motor shaft. There is no separate bearing case.

Columns.Name: DoubleSuctionPumpIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates that the rotor is suspended between two bearings with the fluid entering on either side of the impeller, which is used at higher capacities.

Columns.Name: SelfPrimingPumpIndicator
Columns.Description: The ability of a pump to purge air from its casing and suction hose, creating a partial vacuum and allowing water to flow freely into the pump. Most smaller portable centrifugal pumps (2" to 4" diameter) require an initial manual priming before operation is begun and then operate as self-priming.

Columns.Name: SubmersiblePumpIndicator
Columns.Description: A centrifugal pump designed to operate within the water source being pumped, thereby eliminating the suction lift limitations common to other types.

Columns.Name: CircularCasingPumpIndicator
Columns.Description: Indicates a circular casing, which is used with centrifugal pumps that circulate fluid rather than build head or pressure.

Columns.Name: PumpTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pump Type.

Columns.Name: CentrifugalPumpTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a centrifugal pump type.

Columns.Name: PumpServiceTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump service type.

Columns.Name: BufferFluidTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump buffer fluid type.

Columns.Name: PumpRotationDirectionId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump rotation direction type.

Columns.Name: ImpellerCategoryId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an impeller category.

Columns.Name: PumpMotorTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump motor type.

Columns.Name: PumpApplicationTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump application type.

Columns.Name: PumpDriveTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a pump drive type.

Columns.Name: PumpBearingTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a type of pump bearing.

Columns.Name: FuelTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Fuel Type.

Columns.Name: PipelineStationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Pipeline Station.

Columns.Name: ImpellerSystemTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an impeller type.
